<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF208-218-149  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 218 149.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Oct 24 1989* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Wang first quarter losses total $62 million. (Wang Laboratories)</TITLE><AUTHOR>McCormick, John.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Wang Laboratories Inc. (earnings).andO;Ticker:    WANC.andO;Topic:     Computer industryProfitLossesFirst Quarter.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>WANG FIRST QUARTER LOSSES TOTAL $62 MILLION LOWELL, MASSACHUSETTS, U.S.A.,andO;1989 OCT 18 (NB) -- Financially strapped Wang Laboratories has todayannounced that it had a net operating loss of $62.1 million or 38 cents/shareon sales of $596.8 million for the first quarter of fiscal year 1990, vs aprofit of $13.1 million or 10 cents/share for the same quarter last year.andM;Richard W. Miller, Wang's new president and chief operating officer, saidthat he is pleased with stronger sales that have recently occurred due,according to Mr. Miller, to increased customer confidence.andM;Wang has recently suffered massive losses which led to the replacement ofWang Laboratories' founder An Wang's son by Mr. Miller.andP;  The just-reportedfirst quarter losses were about what were expected by industry observers andWang's stock price has recently started to show signs of a mild recovery.andM;(John McCormick/19891020/Press Contact: Paul G. Henning, Wang Laboratories,508-967-1090)</TEXT></DOC>